b;\">Maximum of 16 points</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 8;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #F4FBFD; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">8. Characteristics of Spouse</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-right: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #F4FBFD; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">Maximum of 16 points</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 9;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #E8F0F3; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">9. Children</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-right: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #E8F0F3; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">Maximum of 8 points</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 10;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #F4FBFD; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">10. Financial Self-Sufficiency</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-right: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #F4FBFD; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">Maximum of 1 point</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"mso-yfti-irow: 11; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #E8F0F3; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">11. Adaptability</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-right: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #E8F0F3; padding: 3.75pt 7.5pt 3.75pt 15.0pt;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #3a454b;\">Maximum of 6 points</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: #231d53;\">Language Proficiency</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">**The Language Proficiency factor takes into account the applicant&rsquo;s knowledge of French and English. Up to 16 points can be awarded for proficiency in French, while only a maximum of 6 points can be awarded for knowledge of English.</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 7.5pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: #231d53;\">Process, Time, and Fees</span></strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">If the applicant is successful in his or her application, the province will issue that applicant a Quebec Selection Certificate. Once having received the QSC, the applicant must then apply to the Canadian federal government in order to be issued their permanent resident status. The federal government is responsible for the applicant&rsquo;s medical and security examinations.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">Processing times vary depending on the many Canadian immigration visa offices around the world.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">Processing fees charged by the province of Quebec has recently risen with the influx of applications over the past few years. The principal applicant must pay a fee of $750, plus an additional $160 for his or her spouse, and $160 for each dependent child.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #333333;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">To know more how you can immigrate to Quebec under Quebec Skilled Worker program contact our experts today.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'Quebec Skilled Worker Program | Immigration Rules & Information', 'Quebec Experience Class, Quebec Skilled Worker Program,', 'The Quebec Experience Class is designed to keep foreign workers and students who have acquired experience in the province of Quebec.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Quebec Skilled Worker Program'),
(17, '2021-09-24 12:50:43', '2021-09-24 18:20:43', '1', '1', '887994617.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nWhat is the Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP)?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP) is a program offered to foreign nationals who have experience and skills in a particular profession. These candidates are provided with the Canadian Permanent Resident Visa on the basis of their abilities to become economically established in Canada. Skilled immigrants are evaluated on the basis of several factors that predict the possibility of being a successful part of Canadian society, such as the applicant\'s age, marital status, work experience, education, language abilities, profile, etc.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Immigrants who reside in Canada on PR visas have the right to live, study and work anywhere in Canada, however they are still the citizens of their home country unless and until they apply for the Citizenship of Canada. There are some requirements to meet by the Permanent residents such as the residency obligation, so as to maintain permanent resident status. Canada\'s permanent residents have been provided with several social benefits like health care, free education, social and unemployment benefits.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Federal Skilled Worker Requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Work Experience</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">In order to qualify for Canadian Immigration and obtain a <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/permanent-residence\">Permanent Resident Visa</a>\r\n, Federal Skilled Worker candidates should have at least 1 year of full-time paid experience in the last 10 years in a specific occupation. In addition to the experience, your job should be under the NOC skill level 0, A, or B. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Education</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The applicants who have studied in Canada must have the educational level from a Canadian High School or Post-Secondary certificate, diploma, or degree. When you have studied outside of Canada, your educational papers must be evaluated by an evaluation agency approved by CIC, Education Credential Assessment (ECA) and their report must confirm that your qualification is equally relevant to the standard of education in Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Language Proficiency</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The language test is a very crucial factor for the applicants. Good command in spoken language will be highly recommended in Canada and for this applicants have to show the language test results in the express entry for the points. The language test needs to be approved by Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC) and the test result is not acceptable if it is more than 2 years old from the date of applying.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Federal Skilled Worker Eligibility Criteria</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">There are particularly 6 selection criteria to check the eligibility of Federal Skilled Workers and all the eligible federal skilled workers have to achieve a minimum score of 67 points. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. <b>Age</b>: For your age, you can gain a maximum of 12 points.<br>2. <b>Education</b>: For FSW programs you can gain a maximum of 25 points.<br>3. <b>Language Skills</b>: Candidates can obtain a maximum of 28 Points for their language skills.<br>4. <b>Work Experience</b>: If you have paid work experience in the last 10 years you can obtain a maximum of 15 points.<br>5. <b>Arranged Employment</b>: For arranged employment, you can gain a maximum of up to 10 points.<br>6. <b>Adaptability</b>: Maximum of 10 points will be rewarded for adaptability.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> FSW Application Procedure</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">It is mandatory that interested candidates have to submit an Express Entry profile to Immigration, Refugees, and Citizenship Canada (IRCC). However, even after submitting an Express Entry profile will not guarantee a candidate will receive Canadian permanent residence. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/crs\">CRS</a> score will be assigned only after submitting an Express Entry profile and be considered in future Express Entry draws for Invitations to Apply (ITAs) for permanent residence.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">While submitting your Express Entry profile, an FSW candidate has to provide the following documents</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Educational Credentials Assessment (ECA)</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A valid ECA report must be provided by an <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/pr/federal-skilled-worker-program\">FSW</a> candidate in order to claim points for education. ECA reports are issued by five organizations in Canada. \r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Language Proficiency Test Results</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Under Express Entry, every applicant must provide results from a foreign language test taken within the last two years. The <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/IELTS\">IELTS</a> exam and the CELPIP exam (available only in Canada) are accepted tests for English. Tests for French proficiency such as the Test d\'Évaluation de Français (TEF) are accepted.\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Identification Documents</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Identification documents must be presented by candidates. Passports should be valid for travel for the candidate and any family members accompanying them.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A candidate will successfully move onto the second stage of the application process if they receive an Invitation to Apply (ITA) for Canadian for permanent residence. In the second stage, the applicant needs to prepare and submit an electronic Application for Permanent Residence (eAPR) within 60 days. </span></span></p><br>', 'Apply for FSW visa through Express Entry', 'Canada PR Visa, Canada FSW Visa, Canadian experience class pr processing time, federal pr processing time, express entry federal skilled worker, express entry federal skilled worker draw, express entry federal skilled worker program', 'Want to apply for a Canada PR visa in the FSW program? Contact Triple I business consultants to get in the express entry pool.', 'federal-skilled-worker-program', 'Can an individual apply directly for permanent residence under the Federal Skilled Worker category?', 'The Federal Skilled Worker category is managed by the Express Entry system, which issues invitations to apply for Canadian permanent residence through regular draws from its pool of candidates. Only those candidates who are issued an Invitation to Apply (ITA) may then submit an application for Canadian permanent residence.', 'Federal Skilled Worker Program'),
(19, '2021-09-24 12:59:03', '2021-09-24 18:29:03', '1', '2', '568051754.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nWhat is the Federal Skilled Trades Program?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Canadian Government initiated the Federal Skilled Trades Program back in 2003. It helps capable immigrants who are experienced and skilled in their respective trades. Canada presents many large sectors such as information and technology, construction, petroleum industry, waste management, and many more.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Employers in Canada are constantly looking for skilled employees to finish mass projects in a given time. The Canadian government is looking for a large number of skilled workers who will assist in developing the Canadian economy through FSTP. To get the best of the Federal Skilled Trades Program (FSTP), you must understand carefully the categories, eligibility, application process, time limit, and everything regarding the program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Benefits of the Federal Skilled Trades Program</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/crs\">Comprehensive Ranking System</a>\r\n (CRS) plays a very key role in Canada Express Entry Program. The higher the CRS score the higher is the possibility of approval for a Canada PR visa.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">However, if you are applying through the Federal Skilled Trades Program, then the CRS cut-off is a little lower in comparison to other express entry programs and a lower CRS score increases your possibility to immigrate to Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A job offer letter from a Canadian employer will be in your hand when you have already decided to immigrate to Canada. The job offer helps you to improve the eligibility criteria and a higher CRS score under the FSTP program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The language eligibility measure is also set lower for FSTP. As a result, it improves the chances of the candidates of FSTP to get an invitation to apply(ITA).</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Federal Skilled Trades Program Eligibility</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. The candidate should have at least 2 years of work experience in a particular nominated occupation in the last 5 years from the date of application.<br>2. The candidate should have good language proficiency in either English or French and for this and has to score well in language ability tests like <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/IELTS\">IELTS</a>, TEF, etc.  In order to qualify for FSTP, applicants must reach a CLB 5 in each of the following areas: writing, listening, reading, and speaking English or French.<br>3. The candidate should be ready to live in any province of Canada except Quebec as it follows its own immigration rules and programs for skilled workers.<br>4. A nominated candidate must meet all the necessities, registered by employers for respective occupations.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">How to apply for the Federal Skilled Trades Program?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If you want to reach Canada through the Federal skilled trades program, then there are two options<br>1. The candidate can apply through the Express Entry program and wait for getting the invitation to apply (ITA) for further rounds of Canada PR visa. This is applicable only to those candidates who have a score of 6 CLB or more on the IELTS exam and have been offered a job under FSTP conditions.<br>2. However, if a candidate possesses job offers under FSTP, but has a lower  IELTS score, is still able to apply through the offline application.<br>3. Precisely fill the information in the application form and provide all the required documents with that. Fill the form without any mistake as the governing bodies offer no second chance for revision subsequent to final submission.<br>4. The processing period is relatively shorter in the Federal government’s program so it takes less than 6 months. But, results may be delayed in case there is any problem in the form or because of incomplete documentation, applicants have to wait longer for ITA.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> FSTP Trades</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Each year, a large number of candidates apply under this program; however, the upper limit for this program is only 3000 applications only. Out of these 300, a maximum of 100 applications is eligible for most of the nominated occupations under this program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p>In general, there are two categories – Category A and Category B.</p>\r\n\r\n<table style=\" width:100%; color: black; font-size:20px; font-family: Georgia, serif;\"> \r\n  <tr>\r\n    <th>Category A</th>\r\n    <th>Category B</th> \r\n   </tr> \r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Electrical and telecommunications</td>\r\n    <td>Welders</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Carpentry trade</td>\r\n    <td>Tooling</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Construction trade</td>\r\n    <td>Structural metal works</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Mechanics trade</td>\r\n    <td>Metal workers</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Supervisors and heavy equipments</td>\r\n    <td>Machining</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Logging and forestry</td>\r\n    <td>Elevators</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Mineral and metal processing</td>\r\n    <td>Crane operators</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>Petroleum industry</td>\r\n    <td>Water well drillers</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n    <td>Waste management</td>\r\n    <td>Underground production miners</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n    <td>Power system</td>\r\n    <td>Petroleum</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n    <td>   </td>\r\n    <td>Iron workers</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n<td>   </td>\r\n<td>Oil and gas</td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n<td>   </td>\r\n<td>Electricians</td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n<td>   </td>\r\n<td>Sheet metal workers</td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n<td>   </td>\r\n<td>Machining and tooling inspections</td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr>\r\n<td>   </td>\r\n<td>Refrigeration and air conditioning mechanics</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>', 'Federal Skilled Trades Program | Triple I Business', 'Federal Skilled Trades Program', 'Federal Skilled Trades Program is basically for skilled workers in pursuit of becoming permanent residents as per their qualification in a skilled trade.', 'federal-skilled-trades-program', NULL, NULL, 'Federal Skilled Trades Program');
