(38, '2021-09-24 13:08:38', '2021-09-24 18:38:38', '1', '3', '1391234574.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> What is the Canadian Experience Class (CEC)?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If you have worked in Canada for at least one year, the Canadian Experience Class (CEC) is an immigration program that allows you to immigrate permanently. CEC is a division of Canada\'s Express Entry immigration system.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Canadian government acknowledges the width of talented workers who are already working in Canada and wish to become <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/permanent-residence\">permanent residents</a>.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Canada Experience Class Advantages</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Under the Express Entry, the Canadian Experience Class candidates have three advantages. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Advantages</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. The Canadian Experience Class enables the <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/crs\">CRS</a>  points to increase if a candidate has a year or more of work experience in Canada.<br>2. The applications get processed quickly ( 3 to 4 months ) under the Canadian Experience Class as the required documentation is minimal.<br>3. If you are a seeker under the Canadian Experience Class then there is no need to show proof of funds such as <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/pr/federal-skilled-worker-program\">FSWC</a> and <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/pr/federal-skilled-trades-program\">FSTC </a>.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Canadian Experience Class-Eligibility Criteria</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Within the last 3 years, the candidate needs to have at least 1 year of full-time skilled work experience in Canada. The experience has to be gained while on a valid <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/work/work-permit-visa\">work permit</a> and needs to be in one or more occupations classified as skill type 0, A, or B under the National Occupational Classification (NOC).<br>2. Is thinking about living outside the province of Quebec.<br>3. Accomplishes the requirement of language levels for the job\r\nper language ability (reading, speaking, listening, and writing). These levels are mentioned below.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The NOC skill level for each of the four languages is:<br>NOC 0 or A CLB 7<br>NOC B CLB 5</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">CEC candidates can go for any of the following IRCC-approved language tests:<br>* CELPIP-General (English)<br>* <a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/IELTS\">IELTS</a>-General (English)<br>* TEF (French)<br>* TCF (French)</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Candidates who verify language ability in both English and French can gain additional points under the CRS.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">How to Apply for a Canadian Experience Class?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Let’s have a look at the 10 steps process to get your Permanent Resident (PR) card. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 1. Obtain a Canadian work permit.</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">For some candidates, an open work permit may be an option who are eligible under the International Experience Canada (IEC) program or the spouse/common-law partner of an international student or foreign worker in Canada. Those who are not classified as workers may be issued employer-specific (\'closed\') permits. Work permits issued with a positive Labour Market Impact Assessment (<a href=\"https://www.tripleibusiness.com/visa/canada/work/labour-market-impact-assessment-(lmia)\">LMIA</a>) and Intra-Company transfers are examples of closed work permits.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 2: Work in Canada for a year</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The candidate needs a minimum of 1 year of work experience to be eligible under the Canadian Experience Class.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 3: Make sure you meet other eligibility requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Candidate needs to go through their language test. For English, candidates need to take the IELTS or CELPIP test, and for French, it is TEF and TCF. Candidates will be awarded extra points if eligible in both English and French.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 4: Create an Express Entry profile</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">All the steps can be completed on the IRCC website. You need to submit some personal information, like your work history, and some of your documentation like your proof of language ability.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 5: Enhance your CRS profile and ranking</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If your CRS score is below the cut-off criteria to receive an ITA then you can consult our guide on how to improve your CRS score.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">An invitation to apply (ITA ) will not be issued to someone whose educational credentials are not proven. This could result in the loss of up to 250 CRS points.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">An applicant who has completed their studies outside Canada can gain points through Educational Credential Assessment (ECA). It\'s better to get an ECA or upload proof of their Canadian education documents to increase the chances of getting an ITA for permanent residence.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The candidate\'s ranking will be increased if their work experience and skills could be in demand in the province, and gain an extra 600-point bonus.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 6: Receive an Invitation To Apply (ITA)</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This step makes the candidate happy, as it allows the candidate and their family, to apply for permanent residence. The candidate will get 60 days to submit the complete application, and once the IRCC conducts one of its draws from the Express Entry pool, ITAs are issued.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If the candidate\'s work permit is about to expire, within the next four months the candidate may apply for an Open Work Permit so that the candidate could continue working in between the process. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 7: Submit an application and provide a medical, background, and security check                 </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">All CEC candidates need to be screened for potential medical and criminal inadmissibility. With the application, the candidate needs to show that he or she has finished a medical exam with an IRCC-recognized panel physician. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Also, the candidate has to provide a police background check (Police clearance certificate) from every country you have lived in for a minimum of six months since the age of 18. You will get 60 days to submit the e-application after receiving an ITA. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 8: Your e-application is assessed </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The submitted e-application will be reviewed by a Canadian immigration officer and let the candidate know if anything else is required. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 9: Verify your permanent residency status and complete your immigration paperwork </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">More than 80 percent of applications take less than 6 months that are submitted under the Canadian Experience Class. Once a candidate is approved, they will receive a confirmation of permanent residence (COPR) document. A document granting permanent residence is signed and dated by a Canadian port of entry official or the IRCC.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Step 10: Get your PR card </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Once the candidate has received the confirmation of status, the candidate can apply for their PR card. In the future, if the candidate travels out of Canada, they can use the PR card as proof of their status in Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Get help with your application </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Triple I Business is devoted to offering quality assistance for the Canadian Experience Class.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">We have designed an Express Entry Roadmap which is designed to inform the candidate about the Express Entry process so that they can make the best decisions when it comes to their immigration. Sign up for the Express Entry Roadmap to get started.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">We are here to help you in preparing an application for Canadian permanent residence. Contact us for the best-in-class services to fulfill your immigration requirement. </span></span></p><br>', 'What is Canadian Experience Class (CEC)?', 'Canadian Experience Class, Express Entry immigration, Workvisa, Canada visa', 'Canadian Experience Class is basically for skilled workers with Canadian work experience and who wish to become permanent residents.', 'canadian-experience-class', NULL, NULL, 'Canadian Experience Class'),
(40, '2021-08-17 09:30:33', '2021-08-17 15:00:33', '2', NULL, '527806938.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nFamily Class Sponsorship Program</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Immigration law in Canada is intended to ensure that families are reunited. Values and family unity are highly emphasized by Canada\'s government. Family reunification is a priority under Canadian immigration law, and various streams reflect that priority.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Quebec Family Class Program is available to those wishing to sponsor a member of the family class to immigrate. Contact our experts to learn more about family class sponsorship options.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Here are a few examples of how families can be sponsored by the Family Class Sponsorship Program:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. Spousal Sponsorship</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Marriage, common law, and conjugal relationships (including same-sex relationships) are included here.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">2. Parent and Grandparent Sponsorship</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Parents or grandparents can be sponsored to immigrate to Canada by citizens or permanent residents.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">3. Parent and Grandparent Super Visa</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A super visa, which can last up to 10 years, is another option for parents and grandparents to visit Canada for up to two years at a time.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">4. Dependent Child Sponsorship and Other Sponsorship</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Canada offers its citizens and permanent residents the opportunity to sponsor their dependent children and live with them in Canada. Adopted children and other orphaned family members are included. Sponsorships can be extended to other family members under exceptional circumstances. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 5. Provincial Family Class Sponsorship</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Other options to consider include Provincial Nominee Programs (PNPs) which offer Family Class Sponsorship options. These programs are provincial and independent of the Federal Family Class Sponsorship Program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Who can be a sponsor?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Applicants who want to immigrate to Canada must be Canadian citizens or permanent residents of Canada at least 18 years of age. In the case of sponsorship by a resident who lives outside of Canada, the sponsor should demonstrate that they will live only in Canada once the sponsored individual becomes a permanent resident.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Both the sponsor and the sponsored should sign an agreement confirming that they understand each other\'s responsibilities and obligations. Those who sponsor family members may even be asked to sign a contract promising to provide: food, clothing, utilities, personal requirements, shelter, fuel, household supplies, dental care, eye care, and health care not covered by the public health plan, for a set period of time. The sponsor should demonstrate sufficient income in case the sponsor\'s sponsored person will bring a dependent child or children with them.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Who cannot be a sponsor?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If any of the following applies to you, you may not be a sponsor:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. You previously sponsored another person and three years have not passed since that person become a permanent resident.<br>2. A reason other than disability prompted you to receive social assistance.<br>3. You are in default of an undertaking, immigration loan, performance bond, or family support payments.<br>4. As a result of a conviction for certain crimes, you haven\'t been pardoned/rehabilitated.<br>5. It has been less than 5 years since you became a Canadian permanent resident after being sponsored as a spouse.<br>6. You have already applied for sponsorship, but the decision has not yet been made.<br>7. A removal order has been issued against you.<br>8. A penal institution (prison, jail, etc.) is holding you.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Two-Step process</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">1. The sponsor must submit their sponsorship application</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The sponsor should initiate the application and include an assessment of the sponsor\'s eligibility under the family class. In order to become a sponsor, the sponsor must submit a separate application.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">2. The foreign national should submit their application for permanent residency </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">An application for permanent residence must be initiated by the foreign national who will be sponsored. In order to qualify for the family class program, foreign nationals must first complete a number of prerequisites, followed by a separate application for permanent residency.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Conditional Permanent Resident Period </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Sponsored spouses, comprising same-sex, common-law spouses and conjugal partners, should live together in a legitimate relationship with their sponsor for minimum of 24 months from the day they received their Canadian Permanent Residency, or else they risk losing their Canadian permanent residency.</span></span></p><br>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This condition applies to any couples who have no common children together and who meet one of the following circumstances:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Those who are married for two years or less<br> 2. Those who have dated for four years, but have been married for two years or less<br> 3. Those who have been in a conjugal relationship with the sponsor for two years or less<br> 4. Those who have cohabited in a common-law relationship for two years or less;</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This condition does not apply if the couple:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Have been married for more than two years<br>2. Have been in a conjugal relationship for more than two years<br>3. Has cohabited in a common-law relationship for more than two years<br>4. They have children in common.\r\n </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">For more information on how you can get sponsored by your family and relatives contact our expert today. Triple I Business is focused to offer high-quality assistance for Family Class Sponsorship Program.</span></span></p><br>', 'All You Need To Know About Family Class Sponsorship Program', 'Family Class Sponsorship Program, Spousal Sponsorship, Parent and Grandparent Sponsorship, Provincial Family Class Sponsorship', 'The Family Class Sponsorship Program allows citizens or permanent residents to sponsor some relatives to immigrate to Canada, thus helpful in reuniting families.', 'family-class-sponsorship-program', NULL, NULL, 'Family Class Sponsorship Program'),
(42, '2021-08-19 11:47:36', '2021-08-19 17:17:36', '3', '5', '660512211.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nQuebec Experience Class Program</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A foreign citizen who has already worked in or studied in Quebec and who wants to immigrate to Quebec can apply for the Quebec Experience Class.\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Students and foreign workers with experience in Quebec will be able to attend the Quebec Experience Class. The Canadian Experience Class provided at the federal level is quite similar, but there are a few differences to be aware of. Your questions can be answered by an immigration lawyer in Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Quebec Experience Class is designed to assist foreign students and workers who have already lived and worked in Quebec in expediting the Canadian immigration process. As with several other Canadian immigration programs, the process for immigration to Quebec consists of two steps. The provincial government of Quebec manages a program called the Quebec Experience Class for foreign nationals who have worked in the province. It is possible for applicants to qualify both as students and as workers at the same time. The Quebec government will issue a Quebec Selection Certificate to successful applicants. The next step for those who receive a Quebec Selection Certificate is to apply for a permanent residency visa with the federal government after a final review of their eligibility has taken place. Canadian permanent residents should submit a Québec Selection Certificate and an application to the Canadian government.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Quebec Experience Class applicants fall into two categories:</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Temporary workers with skilled jobs in Quebec.<br>2. Foreign students who graduated from an institution of higher education in Quebec or are enrolled in an esteemed educational program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">\r\nTemporary workers applying through Quebec Experience Class should meet the following requirements:</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Within the last 24 months, the applicant must have worked in Quebec at a managerial, professional, or technical level (above Skill Level C in the NOC) during that time period.<br>2. Work experience in Quebec should have been based on legal activities.<br>3. The applicant must have had full-time work experience, with a minimum of 30 hours per week. Under the Quebec Experience Class, part-time employment is not eligible.<br>4. A minimum age of 18 is required.<br>5. Applicants must have been working in Québec during the time of their application or maintaining legal status at the time of applying.<br>6. If the work experience is self-employment and the income earned is equal to a full-time salary, the self-employed person may be eligible under the Quebec Experience class.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nUnder Quebec Experience Class, foreign students must meet the following conditions:</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. An applicant is required to have a degree or diploma from a province-recognized educational institution.<br>2. Applicants must have studied for two years or more in Quebec.<br>3. Applicants need to have a proficiency in French which can be proven by a transcript of records or an exam result from an institution recognized by the government of Québec.<br>4. A minimum age of 18 is required.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Contact our experts to learn more about how you can immigrate to Quebec under the Quebec Experience Class. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Providing top-notch assistance for the Quebec Experience Class Program is the main goal of Triple I Business.</span></span></p><br>', 'Quebec Experience Class Program | Canada Immigration', 'Quebec Experience Class, Canada Immigration, Immigration Visa, Workvisa', 'The Quebec Experience Class is for individuals with work experience in Quebec or have studied in Quebec and looking to immigrate to Quebec.', 'quebec-experience-class', 'What is the Quebec Experience Program/Programme de l’expérience Québécoise?', 'The Programme de l\'expérience québécoise (Quebec Experience Program, or PEQ) is a Canadian immigration program prioritizing applicant who have studied or are working in Quebec.', 'Quebec Experience Class'),
(43, '2021-09-11 11:47:24', '2021-09-11 17:17:24', '3', '7', '747953399.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Quebec Investor Immigration Program</span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Quebec immigration program is intended to provide opportunities for people from overseas to come to Canada with a net worth of at least $1,600,000 CAD and invest $800,000 CAD to the federal government for the next five years. The applicant will receive a refund of $800,000 CAD after five years for the investment, but with no interest. Speak to a Canadian immigration expert about your options. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">In order for the applicant to be eligible, the applicant:</span></span></p><br>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. The net worth of the business must be at least $1,600,000 Canadian dollars. If the applicantâs spouse will be accompanying him, then this amount may include assets they own together. However, any money received as a donation will not be included.<br>2. Two years of managerial experience within the last 5 years since application submission. You must have management experience in:<br> A. Legally owned and operated farm, factory, or business.<br>B. An applicant must be employed in a legal professional business that has at least two full-time employees, excepting the applicant\'s position; or<br>C. A government agency or agency of an international organization.<br> 3. In order to participate in the Quebec Investor Program, the applicant must intentionally settle in Quebec and sign an agreement specifying their investment of $800,000 CAD with a financial intermediary authorized to participate.\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Applicants can invest $800,000 in a government-guaranteed framework, where the Canadian government holds the money for five years before returning it to the applicant with zero interest. Investment revenues generated by the program are used to help other Quebec assistance programs for immigrants and minorities.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Assessment of applications will take into account factors such as age, language proficiency, training, and education. The government of Quebec will issue a Quebec Selection Certificate to successful applicants. Following that, the QSC should be submitted with another application to be submitted to the federal government for the essential final review regarding admissibility and for issuing the Canadian permanent resident visa.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Prior to the official evaluation, the application will be evaluated in a preliminary manner to ensure that it is complete. Those who meet the criteria of evaluation are then interviewed by the government after their applications are evaluated. Interviewers will ask about a candidate\'s assets, legal status, and other relevant information acquisition of those assets, the investor agreement, and their management experience.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Contact our experts to explore the choices of Investments and Immigrate on Investor Visas. Triple I Business strives to provide Quebec Investor Immigration Program assistance that is of the highest quality.</span></span></p><br>', 'Quebec Investor Visa | Quebec Immigrant Investor Program', 'Quebec Investor Visa, Quebec Immigrant Investor Program, Canada Immigration', 'The Quebec Immigrant Investor Program is specially designed for immigrant investors looking to apply for Canadian permanent residence and invest in Quebec.', 'quebec-investor-visa', 'What happens with the information I provide in this Quebec Immigrant Investor Program (QIIP) Calculator?', 'The information you provide is only used for the purposes of calculating your potential selection points under the Quebec Immigrant Investor Program. It is not stored or shared with any third parties.', 'Quebec Investor Visa');
