eft: 1pt solid #dddddd; border-image: initial; border-top: none; background: #e8f0f3; padding: 6pt; box-sizing: border-box; text-align: center;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"295\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Roboto\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">Nunavut</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 221.25pt; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; border-right: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; background: #E8F0F3; padding: 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt; box-sizing: border-box;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"295\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 15pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Roboto\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">$29.00</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nHigh-Wage Workers</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The submission of a transition plan is an essential requirement for all Canadian employers who are looking to hire a temporary foreign worker(s) at a wage equal to or higher than the provincial/territorial median hourly wage. In the interest of Canadians, employers are required to develop a plan to reduce their reliance on temporary foreign workers.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nLow-Wage Workers</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The process of completing a Labour Market Impact Analysis (LMIA) does not require employers to submit a transition plan for hiring low-wage workers. Contrary to high-wage workers, low-wage temporary foreign workers are subject to a limit that restricts the number that can be employed by a particular company. There will be a 10% cap on low-wage temporary foreign workers for Canadian employers with more than 10 employees.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">To give Canadian employers time to transition to a Canadian workforce, this cap will be phased in over the next two years.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nLMIA Processing Times</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Processing times for LMIAs can vary from a few weeks to a few months. An LMIA application will be processed by Employment and Social Development Canada (ESDC) within 10 business days. There is now a standard 10-business-day turnaround time for the following categories:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Applications for all LMIA jobs that are in high demand (trades), or<br>2. Top-paying occupations (top 10%)<br>3. (120 days or less) Working periods with short durations.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nLMIA Fees and Additional Employer Requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Application fees for Labour Market Impact Assessments are CDN $1,000 for each application (except for those intended to support permanent residency).  A Privilege Fee of CDN $100 also applies.<br>2. Canadian employers are required to advertise (Canada Job Bank) for a minimum of four weeks prior to applying for LMIA. Additionally, employers must identify at least two other recruitment methods, other than the Canada Job Bank website, to target potential hires.  The ESDC will also be looking for proof that underrepresented groups of Canadians have been considered (e.g. disabled people, aboriginal people, youth).<br>3. To qualify as a requisite for the LMIA, only two languages are acceptable: English and French. A large majority of ESDC agents are reluctant to approve an LMIA application if another language has been used as a determinant other than English or French.</span></span></p><br>', 'What is Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA)', 'Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA), lmia process, lmia work permit, lmia online', 'Labour Market Impact Assessment is a document issued by Employment and Social Development Canada and needed by employers in Canada to hire foreign workers.', 'labour-market-impact-assessment-(lmia)', 'What is a Labour Market Impact Assessment? Is it necessary?', 'The Labour Market Impact Assessment is a document provided by Immigration Canada that a Canadian employer may need to obtain prior to hiring a temporary foreign worker. It is not necessary for some circumstances but it can be for others. It is important for employers to investigate and review LMIA exemption codes to see whether or not they need a Labour Market Impact Assessment. With a positive LMIA, this will indicate that there is a need for a foreign worker to fill the intended position and that no Canadian citizen or permanent resident of Canada can fill the job. A positive LMIA is also referred to as a confirmation letter. After the employer receives a positive LMIA, the temporary foreign worker may then apply for a work permit in Canada. In order to apply for a work permit, the temporary foreign worker will need a valid job offer letter, a contract, a copy of the positive LMIA and the LMIA confirmation number.', 'Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA)'),
(47, '2021-09-16 05:22:48', '2021-09-16 10:52:48', '4', '10', '999212624.jpg', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> NAFTA Work Permits</span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Applicants for a Canadian Temporary Work Permit may qualify for specific exemptions under the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA), which governs bilateral trade between the United States and Mexico.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Mexico and the United States may qualify for a Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA) exemption. However, NAFTA still applies to temporary work visas for Canadians. We can help you decide what is best for you.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> NAFTA-related workstreams include the following </span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. NAFTA Intra-Company Transfers</span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Under NAFTA\'s Intra-Company Transfer program, managers and executives or experts with specialized knowledge can transfer to the Canadian subsidiary, affiliate, or parent branch of a company.  An employee must have been employed by the foreign employer for at least one of the last three years; even better if he or she is employed by the foreign company in the same position as that offered in Canada at the time of application. To inquire about intra-company transfers, contact us. </span></span></p><br>\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">2. NAFTA Traders and Investors</span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Either Canadians or Mexicans can qualify for this category. Traders are those who have an intention to trade substantially between Canada and their home countries. Investment funds should have been committed to a new or prevailing Canadian business by an investor\'s company-owned mainly by American or Mexican citizens. An investment work permit for NAFTA is therefore a requirement for entry into Canada and should be used as a way to expand and guide the Canadian business. Investors may even be able to apply for this category of Work Permits for employees who can be considered key or essential employees.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 3. NAFTA Professionals (TN VISA)</span></strong></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: blackCitizens of the United States and Mexico can apply for a NAFTA Professional Work Permit if they are qualified to work in one of the vocations listed by Citizenship and Immigration Canada. In case the Canadian job is extended, or in case the NAFTA Work Permit is then renewed, these permits are available for a period of up to 3 years. Québec employers who qualify or qualify for NAFTA professional work permits.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Within NAFTA guidelines, there are credentials that are required rather than education requirements. Academic credentials and work experience may need to be provided.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">NAFTA Professionals are required to have pre-set Canadian employment, matching their qualifications. NAFTA professionals do not have to meet the LMIA requirement, which simplifies their job search in Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Get a NAFTA work permit from our experts.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Triple I Business has the aim to provide premium quality assistance for the NAFTA Work Permits.</span></span></p><br>', 'NAFTA Work Permit Canada | NAFTA-related workstreams', 'NAFTA Work Permits, NAFTA Intra-Company Transfers, NAFTA Traders and Investors, TN VISA', 'NAFTA Work Permit offers special opportunities for citizens of the U.S. and Mexico to work in Canada without the need for LMIA.', 'nafta-work-permits', NULL, NULL, 'NAFTA Work Permits');
