(48, '2021-08-25 11:43:36', '2021-08-25 17:13:36', '4', '11', '1126352655.png', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> \r\nCanada Work Permit Visa </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">For most people seeking employment in Canada, a work permit is required. Join the above 180,000 foreign workers who come to work in Canada each year by applying for a Canadian Work Permit.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Get in touch with our consultants today to learn more about:  </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. An overview of how to apply for work permits<br>2. Work Permits: Duration<br>3. A valid Open Work Permit<br>4. Exemption from work permit</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> The steps to getting a Canadian work permit</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">In general, obtaining a work permit in Canada involves two steps. Prior to applying for a Canadian work permit, applicants will typically need a job offer.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">\r\nStep 1</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">A Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA) is usually the first step toward obtaining a Canadian work permit from Employment and Social Development Canada (ESDC). Canadian employers should generally seek to fill positions domestically and demonstrate that any Canadian citizens or permanent residents do not qualify.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">\r\nStep 2</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The applicant can apply for a Canadian work permit once the LMIA has been granted.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Work permits are employer-specific until a worker has an open work permit. If an employee wants to change employers in Canada, they will need to obtain another Work Permit. The duration of Canadian work permits is also limited.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">For both Canadian employers and temporary foreign workers, we handle the entire Canadian Work Permit process.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">\r\nWork Permit Duration</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Each Canadian work permit expires after a certain period of time.  If you\'re interested in working in Canada permanently, or for an indefinite period, you must apply for permanent resident status first.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Non-Canadians are restricted in how long they can work in Canada for the duration of their permits and accumulation of time at their disposal for work in Canada. In total, a Canadian is permitted to work in Canada for 48 consecutive months, or for 4 years total.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">When all four years of work have been completed, foreign workers must leave Canada for a minimum of 48 months (4 years) before being able to reenter the country.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">\r\nOpen Work Permit Canada</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"fIn contrast to a regular work permit, an open work permit does not specify a particular job or employer. Canadian Work Permits usually refer to both the job and the employer, thus restricting the holder to working under those conditions. Its holder may provide services to nearly any Canadian employer in any capacity with an Open Work Permit.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The applicant for a work permit with a no-work offer requirement does not have to complete a positive Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA).</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">According to Canadian immigration regulations, Open Work Permits may be requested by:</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Temporary foreign workers\' spouses or common-law partners with occupations of level 0, A, or B, as defined in the National Occupation Classification (NOC).<br>2. Students who are engaged in full-time studies with their spouses, common-law partners, or common-law children.<br>3. Graduates of Canadian post-secondary institutions who are international students.</span></span></p><br>\r\n \r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0