(119, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '4', '9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'How do I know whether or not I need an Labour Market Impact Assessment in order to hire a temporary foreign worker?', 'This is a very important and common question that many Canadian employers have. There are two ways in order to find out whether or not you need a Labour Market Impact Assessment prior to hiring a temporary foreign worker. First, you may review the list of LMIA exemption codes. Second, you may contact an International Mobility Worker Unit (IMWU) for assistance. Additionally, when you contact IMWU, you may request their opinion on whether you need an LMIA for your temporary foreign worker, so long as the temporary foreign worker is from a country that is visa-exempt and they are currently outside of Canada.', NULL),
(120, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '4', '9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'If I received a Labour Market Impact Assessment one year ago, am I required to obtain another one?', 'This entirely depends on whether you are hiring the foreign worker after the LMIA from a year ago has expired. LMIAs are often valid for only a 6 month time period. Therefore, if you have not hired a temporary foreign worker within the 6 months, then you will need to obtain another one. At this point, when applying for another LMIA, Employment and Social Development Canada (ESDC) will once again analyze whether there are still no Canadian citizens or permanent residents of Canada that can fill the intended position.', NULL),
(121, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '4', '9', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'I have not received a new Labour Market Impact Assessment from my current employer and my work permit is about to expire?', 'This is a tricky situation. However, thankfully there is an answer. You may only submit your work permit extension application without a Labour Market Impact Assessment only if your work permit will expire within 2 weeks. If your work permit’s expiry date more than 2 weeks away, you must wait to receive your Labour Market Impact Assessment. However, if your expiry date is 2 weeks away, you must also submit proof that the LMIA was requested. Specifically, you will need to include a copy of the application sent to ESDC or; a copy of the receipt confirmation number if the request was submitted online or; indicate in the section “Details of Intended Work in Canada” of the work permit application: the date the LMIA was sent, the office in which it was sent to, the employer’s name and the confirmation number for the submission, if you have it. Additionally, you must also contact the Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC) Call Centre with the LMIA confirmation number within 2 months of submitting your application.', NULL),
(122, '2021-08-04 17:51:28', '2021-08-05 06:21:28', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'What is the main difference between Universities and Colleges in Canada?', 'Universities get to deal independently with academic matters regarding the curricula, methods and teaching strategies. Universities have the power to set academic, admission, and graduation policies and standards, appoint staff, and undertake academic planning, meanwhile Private Universities are out-of-province institutions permitted to provide degrees after a meticulous quality assessment process by the designated governmental authorities which give the green light to certain degrees.', NULL),
(123, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'What are the common requirements into getting accepted in a Canadian University/College?', 'In order to get admitted in a Canadian tertiary education institution there are requirements students will have to meet, whether it I an undergraduate or a postgraduate program. Depending on the field of studies, programs and other relevant factors competition can vary. The two essential criteria are however, high school grades/performance as well as language skills be it English (in most of the provinces) or French in francophone ones.', NULL),
(124, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'What are the chances of getting a postgraduate degree after you’ve graduated from a Canadian post-secondary educational institution?', 'Once you’ve completed a BA degree in a Canadian tertiary institute you are more than welcome to continue your postgraduate studies in this country, having full legal support from the Canadian authorities regarding migration policies.', NULL),
(125, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'How long does it take to get a Master degree in Canada?', 'Commonly, Master degrees last for a whole academic year including an obligatory internship added to the overall duration. Sometimes a Master degree can last for two academic years, depending on the curricula and the sensitivity of the program.', NULL),
(126, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'How long does it take to get a PhD degree in Canada?', 'PhD degree programs are commonly two to three years in duration, are separately funded and considered as a job position (not always), in the majority of the cases.', NULL),
(127, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'What type of documentation will I need in order to apply for a student visa in Canada?', 'Applicants are generally required:  Proof of acceptance and enrolment to an accredited academic institution in Canada; Possess a valid passport/travel document, and provide proof of financial support; Ties to their home country and evidence of their intention to leave Canada at the end of their studies. Additionally, students have to have proof of no criminal history or endangering medical conditions of any sort and willingly undergo medical testing as required.', NULL),
(128, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Where can I purchase health insurance as an international student in Canada?', 'Usually the deal is undergone through the University they chose to attend, it all depends on the province. In some provinces international student might not be included in the public health insurance plan therefore they must purchase private health insurance. It is different in every province, however a rough estimate would be 500 CAD per year.', NULL),
(129, '2021-01-16 19:50:57', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'What are the alternatives for short-term accommodation in Canada?', 'Numerous hotels are at ones disposal once you arrive at your Canadian destination. Opposed to more expensive hotels, a hostel is the perfect low-budget temporary accommodation in a big city. Another alternative for a short stay would be a Bed-and-Breakfast entity.', NULL),
(130, '2021-01-16 20:13:46', '2021-01-17 01:20:57', '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FAQ (Student Visa)', 'FAQ (Student Visa)', 'FAQ (Student Visa)', '', 'Do I need Health insurance if I want to study in Canada?', 'As for international students in Canada, they must all have health insurance one way or the other', 'FAQ (Student Visa)'),
(133, '2021-07-12 09:47:41', '2021-07-12 15:17:41', '5', '17', '1687404011.png', NULL, '<h1 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black;\"> Quebec Entrepreneur Program</span></strong></h1>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\"><b>The Quebec Entrepreneur Program</b> focuses on attracting business people who wish to establish or invest in an acceptable business venture. Interested foreign entrepreneurs may be granted special entry into Canada for an &ldquo;exploratory visit&rdquo;.</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">An experienced consultant from our Canadian immigration consultancy can discuss your options.</span></span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black;\"> Quebec Entrepreneur Program Eligibility</span></strong></h2><br>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">Applicants must meet the following general requirements in order to be eligible for the Quebec Entrepreneur Program:</span></p><br>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the applicant must have net assets of at least $300,000 CAD, which have been legally obtained. This amount may include the assets of the applicant&rsquo;s spouse (including common law spouse) provided that the spouse will be accompanying the applicant.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">The applicant must at least have two years of management experience running a business acquired within the past years from the day the application is submitted. The experience must have been in a business that was both legal and profitable (agricultural, industrial or commercial) and the applicant must have been managing the business alone or with their spouse, while controlling at least 25% of the business&rsquo; capital equity.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">&ldquo;Business&rdquo; is defined as a business involved in agricultural, industrial or commercial activities.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">&ldquo;Experience running a business&rdquo;. The applicant must meet the definition of management experience, by demonstrating that they were responsible and assumed full-time duties for all major aspects of running the business&nbsp; (such as management and control of materials, financial and human resources). Experience from apprenticeships do not count.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">&ldquo;Full-time&rdquo;. The applicant must meet the definition of &ldquo;full-time&rdquo;, by demonstrating that they devoted all their working time to management.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">The applicant must intend on living and starting the proposed business in the province of Quebec.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black;\">Starting a Business vs. Acquiring a Business</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">The Quebec Entrepreneur program has two components for the applicant to choose from which depends upon whether the applicant wishes to start a business in Quebec or purchase a business in Quebec. Whether the applicant wishes to start a business or buy an existing business in Quebec, the applicant (and the applicant\'s spouse if applicable) should own minimum 25% of the capital equity of the business they intend to start or acquire in Quebec. Applicants who want to start their own business should manage the business themselves or with their spouse. Applicants who acquire a business should manage the business by themselves or being a partner in the management and the operations of the business (on a day to day basis).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">The Quebec Entrepreneur Program will even consider additional factors like:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the applicant&rsquo;s age</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the nature and duration of the applicant&rsquo;s training</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">language skills</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">personal qualities and knowledge of Quebec</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">steps taken towards either purchasing or acquiring a business in Quebec</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the applicant&rsquo;s ability to carry out a business project (key aspect of the assessment)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; color: black;\">Compliance</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">When the applicant arrives in Quebec, the applicant should abide by the following conditions for at least one of three years after being granted their Canadian permanent residency:</span></p><br>\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0cm;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the applicant must follow through with his or her plan to purchase or acquire an acceptable business with a minimum ownership of 25% of capital equity with a value of at least $100,000.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">The business must employ a Quebec resident other than the applicant or the applicant&rsquo;s family member on a full-time basis (minimum of 30 hours per week). The agriculture entrepreneur is not obligated to create or maintain full-time employment.</span></li><br>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; margin-top: 3.75pt; margin-bottom: 3.75pt; line-height: normal; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;\">the applicant must participate in the daily management and operations of the business.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: \'Georgia\',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black;\">To know more how you can immigrate to Quebec under the Quebec Entrepreneur Program, contact our experts today. <b>Triple I Business</b> offers premium assistance for <b>the Quebec Entrepreneur Program.</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \'Georgia\',serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'Quebec Entrepreneur Program | Eligibility | Business | Entrepreneurs', 'Quebec Entrepreneur Program, Canada immigration, Entrepreneurs', 'The Québec Entrepreneur program is designed for qualified business owners and entrepreneurs who want to establish or acquire a business.', 'quebec-entrepreneur-program', NULL, NULL, 'Quebec Entrepreneur Program'),
(134, '2021-09-24 13:20:00', '2021-09-24 18:50:00', '8', NULL, '789219473.jpg', NULL, '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> British Columbia provincial nominee program</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">BC Provincial Nominee Program ( BC PNP ) is the best way for entrepreneurs, investors, high-net-worth individuals, and skilled workers to get permanent residency in Canada. British Columbia PNP allows you to quickly obtain PR in the province, which leads to Canadian citizenship.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> BC PNP Entrepreneur Immigration Eligibility Criteria</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Should have a personal net worth of at least $600,000.<br>2. Should be able to Invest a minimum of $200,000 in a new or existing business in British Columbia.<br>3. Should have at least one new full-time position for a Canadian citizen or permanent resident in the company.<br>4. Should have a Canadian Language Benchmark Level 4 in Either English or French, Which Includes listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills.<br>5. Should have experience in business or management on a senior level.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Document Required</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The documentation and other requirements for British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program for Entrepreneurs include:<br>1. Having a private net worth of a minimum of CAD$600,000.<br>2. Demonstrate business or management experience.<br>3. Have legal status in Canada or eligible to obtain Canadian citizenship.<br>4. Build a new business or purchase and improve an existing business.<br>5. Make an eligible personal investment of a minimum of CAD$200,000 within the business.<br>6.Create a minimum of one new full-time job for a Canadian citizen or permanent resident within the business.<br>7. Passport & travel history.<br>8. Education and business credentials.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> British Columbia PNP Processing Time for Entrepreneurs</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">BC Provincial Nominee Program (BC PNP) has an estimated processing period of 4 months for Entrepreneur Immigration.<br>1. If you\'re nominated, and if any of the subsequent apply, you\'ll have to submit a post-nomination request:<br>2. If you\'ve been promoted, changed employers, been terminated, laid off, placed on extended leave, or if your employer has closed or changed Ownership.<br>3. If your working papers will expire within 180 days.<br>4. If your family makeup has changed (i.e., A recent marriage, divorce, legal separation, childbirth, etc.).<br>5. If your application for PR is returned as incomplete (under section 10 of the IRPR). Only in exceptional circumstances may a nominator receive further consideration by the British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> BC PNP Tech Immigration</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Through the BC PNP immigration program, applicants in high-demand tech occupations can apply for provincial nominations with expedited processing.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Eligibility</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Candidates for the BC PNP Tech program must be registered in one of the BC Skills Immigration programs and work in one of the 29 in-demand tech occupations identified by the BC PNP.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Processing Time</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Our team prioritizes applications for 29 Key technology occupations. After an employer applies, their files get assigned to a dedicated processing team within one working day.<br><br>The majority of BC PNP applications are processed within two months of receipt, while BC PNP Tech applications get typically processed within a few weeks.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Application Procedure</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">To apply for the BC PNP Tech program, a foreign national must verify that the candidate meets the National Occupation Classification (NOC) code requirements for one of the 29 in-demand occupations. After matching the Requirements, the candidate can start the application process by creating a profile on BC PNP Online.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Job Offer</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The job offer you submit must fit in one of 29 in-demand occupations to qualify for the Tech program. The Offer must be valid for at least one year. The applicant must have at least 120 days left on their existing contract if They are employed already by the company to which they get considered.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> How Will Triple I Business Help?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">At Triple I Business, we have the expertise to help you navigate the difficulties of these programs and help you choose correctly. We help you with:<br>1. Required documents for the immigration.<br>2. Complete processing of your application.<br>3.  \r\n\r\nFilling out forms, submitting documentation, and filing applications.<br>4. Timely Updates & follow-up on the process.<br>5. Assistance in finding jobs in Canada.<br><br>With our years of experience in immigration, Triple I Business can help you file an application that has the highest chance of success. Contact one of our consultants today for guidance.</span></span></p><br>', 'British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program | Eligibility | How To Apply', 'British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program, BC PNP, BC eligibility, BC processing time, BC job offer', 'Apply for British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program for Canadian citizenship for high skilled and experienced workers. Check eligibility', 'British Columbia provincial nominee program (BC PNP)', NULL, NULL, 'British Columbia provincial nominee program'),
(140, '2021-08-14 05:24:29', '2021-08-14 10:54:29', '8', NULL, '1838684541.jpg', 'Saskatchewan-immigrant-nominee-program', '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Saskatchewan Nominee Programme-SINP </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The SINP immigration program is responsible for its growing economy. Saskatchewan has a booming economy that relies mainly on agriculture and mining. <br>Saskatchewan Immigration Nominee Program (SINP) offers a way for individuals looking to immigrate to Canada to be considered for priority status through the Express Entry program if they are in a position to make a meaningful contribution to economic growth. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> SINP Category </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">There are four categories under Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. International Skilled Worker<br>2. Worker With Saskatchewan Work Experience<br> 3. Entrepreneur<br>4. Farm Owner & operator</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. SINP International Skilled Worker: </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Overskilled worker who wishes to live and work in Saskatchewan which is further divided into 3 sub-categories.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> A. For those who have a valid job offer from a Saskatchewan employer in a skilled occupation </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Eligibility:\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. You must be residing outside of Canada, have proof of your legal status in Canada, and not be a refugee claimant.<br>2. The Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program (SINP) point evaluation requires a minimum of 60 points.<br>3. Have at least a year of work experience in the past ten years. <br>4. Have at least a CLB 4 (Canadian Language Benchmark) language score.<br>5. Be eligible for Saskatchewan licensing.<br>6. Possess an offer for a permanent, full-time job in Saskatchewan. You will need a legitimate SINP Job Approval Letter to show as proof. <br>7. Health Professionals can apply under the Health Professionals sub-category, while Food and Beverage Servers/Persons can apply under the Hospitality Sector Project sub-category.\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> B. For those without a job offer who are highly skilled and highly in demand in Saskatchewan </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Eligibility:\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. You must be residing outside of Canada, have proof of your legal status in Canada, and not be a refugee claimant.<br>2. Score at least 60 out of 110 on the SINP assessment grid.<br>3. Have a language score of a minimum of 4 – Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB).<br>4.Have completed post-secondary education, training, or internship that\'s equivalent to that in Canada.<br>5. For education outside of Canada, you must submit an educational credential assessment (ECA) from a favored organization.<br>6. Candidates must apply for Saskatchewan Licensure if they have completed trades or job training as part of their high school education.<br>7. Should have work experience that is highly skilled and not on the Excluded Occupation List.<br> 8. You must have at least one year of full-time paid work experience in a skilled occupation over the past ten years and should be related to your field of education. At the time of your application, your work experience must be in a high skilled occupation (NOC \"0\", \"A\" or \"B\") which needs to be in demand in Saskatchewan.<br>9. Your work experience must be co-related to your occupation and education.<br>10. You must provide evidence of your professional status or eligibility to be licensed. <br>11. Make sure you have all the required documents in your application. You will not receive a refund for an incomplete application.<br> 12. Should be able to show the proof of settlement funds and a settlement plan.\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> C. For those who wish to live and work in Saskatchewan & have applied in the Canada Immigration Express Entry pool.\r\n </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Eligibility:\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Should have an officially acceptable Express Entry Profile Number and Job Seeker Code.<br>2. Require a minimum of 60 points on SINP\'s point assessment grid.<br>3. Have a language test result that meets the requirements of federal Express Entry language.<br>4. Have completed post-secondary school or training that is equivalent to at least one year of Canadian education. <br>5. For all education outside Canada, the candidate must submit an educational credential assessment (ECA) from the list of approved organizations of IRCC.<br> 6. The candidate who has completed training as part of high school is not required to submit an ECA but must still apply for Saskatchewan licensure.<br> 7.Hold an experience in a job that is not on the Excluded Occupation List. <br> 8. The minimum need for work experience is as follows:<br>a. For skilled professionals: At least one year of work experience in the past ten years.<br>b. Skilled Tradesmen must have worked in a skilled trade for at least two years in the previous five years.<br>c. Should have a minimum of one year of work experience in Canada in the past three years.<br>9. Your work experience should be in the field of your completed post-secondary education or training.<br>10. For more information on whether your job profile requires specific SINP education requirements, please refer to SINP Requirements Related to Professional Status or Licensure.<br>11. Must carry a Professional Status or evidence of eligibility for Licensure for your job.<br>12. Provide settlement funds and a settlement plan.\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 2. SINP Worker With Saskatchewan Work Experience:</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\"> Skilled workers living and have gained experience from a Saskatchewan employer under a valid work permit can apply through this program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Eligibility:\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. An employer in Saskatchewan has offered a full-time permanent position. The job must be in a trade or fall within the National Occupation Classification (NOC) Matrix A, B, or O.<br>2. Apply under the subcategory Hospitality Sector Pilot Project for Food and Beverages.<br>3. Have a legitimate SINP Job Approval Letter.<br>4. Work under the employer who offered you the job with a valid work permit for more than six months. <br>5. If you are applying for a job in a NOC C occupation, you will need to score at least a four on the Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB).<br>6. If your profession is regulated in Saskatchewan, you should show that you meet the licensing requirements. Also, check out the regulations for licensure requirements for regulated occupations.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 3. SINP Entrepreneur:</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\"> The Saskatchewan Entrepreneur is one of the categories of the Provincial Nominee Program(PNP), operated by the province of Saskatchewan. In this, they target experienced and senior business managers who are willing to start a new business or buy an existing business for day-to-day management duties.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">4. Farm Owner & Operator SINP: </span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">In the Farm Owners & Operator SINP program they target experienced farm owners & operators who are willing to own & operate a farm in Saskatchewan.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Eligibility:\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. You should be able to provide financial documents that show a net worth of $500,000 (CAD).<br>2. To purchase and operate a farm in Saskatchewan you have to sign a Performance Agreement. You must also put $75,000 (CAD) in trust, which will be repaid after the Performance Agreement\'s requirements have been satisfied. The deposit will be returned to the government if you do not satisfy the requirements within two years of relocating to Saskatchewan.<br>3. For at least ten working days you have to make an exploratory visit to Saskatchewan.<br>4. To prove that you are an experienced farm operator you must provide valid documentation which will be further verified through an interview.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Benefits: </span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Being a part of Saskatchewan provides you some benefits as mentioned below-</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. The cost of education is very less in comparison to other provinces.<br>2. The Housing costs are also lower than other provinces and cities in Canada.<br>3. If you are a resident of Saskatchewan you will get Health care services. The government provides all medical & hospital insurance plans.<br>4. You get public transportation which is affordable and safe.<br>5. Tax benefits throughout Canada tax charges in Saskatchewan are the lowest.<br>6. You are eligible at the age of 49 years.\r\n.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">How To Apply\r\n </span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The following are the two ways of applying to SINP.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Step 1: Apply For Nomination</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Aspirants must prepare the application package that includes federal & provincial forms, supporting documents and submit a completed application to ‘SNIP Apply Online’ by paying the corresponding fee.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Step 2: Visa Application</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The application will be assessed based on various eligibility criteria, and only the approved candidates will get nominated to the IRCC.<br>Within 30 Days the selected Saskatchewan Express Entry applicants must accept the SINP nomination via their Express Entry account, the IRCC will extend an Invitation to Apply (ITA) for permanent residence. Within 60 days of receiving the ITA for permanent residence must be submitted to IRCC.<br>After due verification, the PR visa will be granted to the primary applicant and accompanying family members.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">  Application Processing Times for SINP\r\n</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The processing time is updated every quarter (three months). Processing times can change from time to time and are not always a precise prediction for future applications. Below you will find the average processing time it takes for SNIP in each category.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> How Will Triple I Business Help?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">At Triple I Business, we have the expertise to help you navigate the difficulties of these programs and help you choose correctly. We help you with:<br>1. Required documents for the immigration.<br>2. Complete processing of your application.<br>3.  \r\n\r\nFilling out forms, submitting documentation, and filing applications.<br>4. Timely Updates & follow up on the process.<br>5. Assistance in finding jobs in Canada.<br>With our years of experience in immigration, Triple I Business can help you file an application that has the highest chance of success. Contact one of our consultants today for guidance.</span></span></p><br>', 'Saskatchewan Nominee Programme-SINP | Eligibility | How To Apply', 'Saskatchewan Nominee Programme-SINP, SINP eligibility, SINP Apply, SINP processing time, SINP job offer.', 'Saskatchewan Nominee Programme targets potential immigrants with skills and experience in high-demand occupations in Saskatchewan.', 'Saskatchewan-immigrant-nominee-program', NULL, NULL, 'Saskatchewan-immigrant-nominee-program');
