(142, '2021-08-14 05:28:11', '2021-08-14 10:58:11', '8', NULL, '1068962648.png', 'Ontario immigration nominee program', '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP)</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Ontario\'s Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) is Ontario\'s economic immigration program. Ontario is the most developed province in Canada due to its large corporations and start-ups, so most people wish to settle here. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The OINP accepts applications from international workers, international students, and other interested individuals who have the appropriate skills, experience, and education.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Ontario PNP Category</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Ontario Provincial Nominee Program offers foreign nationals a chance to become permanent residents of Canada. The province has divided its immigration streams among three categories:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Ontario Human Capital<br>2. Ontario Employer Job Offer<br>3. Ontario Business</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. Ontario Human Capital</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This stream targets candidates for Ontario’s labor force who have valuable work experience, education, proficiency in both English and French, and have a profile in Canada’s Express Entry system. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Ontario\'s Human Capital is again subdivided into two categories, i.e., The international graduate stream and the Ontario Express Entry stream. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">International Graduate</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">You must create a profile in the OINP e-Filing Portal to qualify under the Master\'s Graduate or Ph.D. Graduate streams. After getting an Invitation to Apply(ITA), apply within two years of getting your graduate degree from an eligible Ontario university.<br>1. Masters Graduate stream<br>2. Ph.D. Graduate stream\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Ontario’s Express Entry streams</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Express Entry System of the federal government manages this stream. You must receive a notification of interest from Ontario and have an updated profile in the federal government\'s Express Entry system with your current job experience, language abilities, and education to qualify for Ontario\'s Express Entry streams.<br>1. French-Speaking Skilled Worker stream<br>2. Human Capital Priorities stream<br>3. Skilled Trades stream</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 2. Ontario Employer Job Offer</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This stream will provide immigration options for candidates who have a valid job offer from an Ontario employer. Applicants must also meet specific eligibility requirements depending on which stream they wish to apply through. Both the employer and the job must meet certain criteria to be considered valid.<br>1. Foreign Worker<br>2. International Student with a Job Offer<br>3. In-Demand Skills\r\n.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">3. Ontario Business</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This immigration is a collection of streams designed to invite wealthy entrepreneurs who are interested in investment in business development in Ontario. Through this program, entrepreneurs can launch new business projects in Ontario & if the projects are successful, the applicants will be nominated for Canadian permanent residence.<br>1. Entrepreneur<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> OINP Application process</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">An applicant can apply in Ontario PNP through the express entry and must have the following requirements<br>1. Your profile must be in action in Express Entry Pool<br>2. You must have experience under NOC code skill levels O, A & B.\r\n3. You must have a minimum of 67 points out of 100 and 6 bands in each module of IELTS.<br>4. You should have sufficient funds to support yourself and your family while you are in Ontario.<br>5. A job offer letter can be an additional benefit for you.\r\n6. You Must receive NOI from Ontario.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Ontario PNP Processing Time</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Ontario PNP takes around 60-90 days which is faster than other Provincial Nominee Programs. However, the processing time differs from person to person & on the validity and accuracy of individual documents.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> How can Triple I business Help</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">At Triple I Business, we have the expertise to help you navigate the difficulties of these programs and help you choose correctly. We help you with:<br><br>1. Required documents for the immigration.<br>2. Complete processing of your application.<br>3.\r\nFilling out forms, submitting documentation, and filing applications.<br>4. Timely Updates & follow up on the process<br>5. Assistance in finding jobs in Canada.<br><br>With our years of experience in immigration, Triple I Business can help you file an application that has the highest chance of success. Contact one of our consultants today for guidance.\r\n</span></span></p><br>', 'Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) | OINP Application Process', 'Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) | OINP Application Process  OINP Categories | OINP Human Capital | OINP Business | ONIP Employer job offer | OINP Processing Time', 'Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) is for international students and workers who want to settle in Ontario. OINP has three different categories.', 'Ontario immigration nominee program', NULL, NULL, 'Ontario immigration nominee program'),
(143, '2021-08-14 05:28:36', '2021-08-14 10:58:36', '8', NULL, '1131512903.png', 'Atlantic immigration pilot program', '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Introduced in 2017, the Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program allows international students and skilled workers who want to reside in Atlantic Canada with their families. The aim is to build a skilled workforce and improve the employment rates across this province.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program has three programs:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Atlantic High Skilled Program (AHSP)<br>2. Atlantic Intermediate Skilled Program (AISP)<br>3. Atlantic International Graduate Program (AIGP)\r\n\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Eligibility Criteria For AIPP</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">If you are willing to relocate to Canada through AIPP, a candidate must have the following. The eligibility will be different for each category.<br><br>1. Applicants must either be a recent graduate from a publicly-funded institution in Atlantic Canada or a skilled worker who meets all other program requirements. Under each category, the requirements related to skill level, educational qualification, language proficiency, and work experience are different if applicable.<br>2. Be living abroad or temporarily residing in Canada.<br>3. Receive a valid job offer from a designated employer in one of the four Atlantic provinces.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. Atlantic High Skilled Program (AHSP)</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Under this program, eligible foreign workers can submit a permanent residence application to Canada with an offer of employment from an employer in Atlantic Canada.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Eligibility</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Should have worked for at least 1 year in management, professional, or technically skilled jobs.<br>2. Holds a high school diploma/degree from Canada.<br>3. Take a language fluency test.<br>4. Proof of funds to showcase sustenance</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Atlantic Intermediate Skilled Program (AISP)</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This program is designed for candidates seeking jobs that require a high-school education and/or job-specific training.\r\n\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Eligibility</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Have worked in a job that requires you to have a high school education and job-specific training for a minimum of 1 year to get a Canada Permanent Residency Visa and the other requirement as mentioned in AHSP.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Atlantic International Graduate Program (AIGP)</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">This program is specifically designed for people who have graduated from an Atlantic province public-funded institution with a degree, diploma, or other credentials<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Eligibility</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Hold a degree or diploma from an authorized institute that is publicly funded in the province of Atlanta.<br>2. Be able to demonstrate that you have lived in the Atlantic province for a minimum of 16 months during the two-year period before receiving a degree, diploma, or credential.<br>3. Take a test to display fluency in English and French.<br>\r\n\r\n4. There is no requirement for work experience for international graduates who are hired via Atlantic Immigration progress.<br>\r\n\r\n5. You must have a job offer made using the offer of employment to Foreign National Form.<br>\r\n\r\n6. This job must be full-time, nonseasonal and under skill/type level o, A, B, or C under the National Occupational Classification (NOC).<br>7. This job should provide you employment for a minimum of 1 year.<br>8. The employer should have a Confirmation of Designation from the provinces.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Benefits Of AIPP </span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. The Atlantic provinces have stable local economies that need to be sustained by immigrant intake.<br>2. The processing time for a visa application under the AIPP is the same as the Express Entry Program.<br>3. The unemployment rate is gradually improving. In comparison, the cost of living in Atlantic Canada is lower than in other populated provinces.<br>4. A candidate can apply for a temporary work permit and begin working in Canada while their Canada PR Visa is still in process.<br>5. A variety of job opportunities can be explored in Canada\'s Atlantic provinces. Thus, migrants with a range of professional interests are able to explore career opportunities in the region.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Processing Time</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">IRCC typically aims to process 80% of the Atlantic Immigration Pilot Programs similar to the Express Entry selection system. But said that, the AIPP application will be separately processed from that of Express Entry applications. Applicants will be enrolled based on first come first served.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> How can Triple I business Help</span></strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">At Triple I Business, we have the expertise to help you navigate the difficulties of these programs and help you choose correctly. We help you with:<br><br>1. Required documents for the immigration.<br>2. Complete processing of your application.<br>3. \r\n\r\nFilling out forms, submitting documentation, and filing applications.<br>4.Timely Updates & follow up on the process\r\n\r\nAssistance in finding jobs in Canada.<br><br>With our years of experience in immigration, Triple I Business can help you file an application that has the highest chance of success. Contact one of our consultants today for guidance. \r\n\r\n</span></span></p><br>', 'Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program | Eligibility | Processing Time', 'Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program, AIPP Eligibility, AIPP Benefits, AIPP Processing Time, AIPP Types', 'AIPP is one of the best PNP programs for international students and skilled workers. It has three programs. Check its eligibility and processing time.', 'Atlantic immigration pilot program', NULL, NULL, 'Atlantic immigration pilot program'),
(144, '2021-08-14 05:29:25', '2021-08-14 10:59:25', '8', NULL, '42233200.png', 'Prince Edward island PNP', '<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Prince Edward Island PNP</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Prince Edward Island is the smallest province of Canada located on the east coast of North America. This is considered one of the best places to live, study, work, and raise a family. Candidates who wish to settle in PEI can make it possible by applying to the Provincial Nominee Program (PNP). </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The PEI PNP is divided into 3 categories:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. PEI Express Entry<br>2. PEI Labour Impact<br>3. PEI Business Impact</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. PEI Express Entry</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Immigrants who are in the federal Express Entry pool and are looking to work in Prince Edward Island province may be eligible for PEI Express Entry. However only candidates with relevant skills and work experience that match the province’s current labour needs will be considered for Express Entry PNP.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Express Entry Requirement</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">To be eligible for the PEI PNP Express Entry stream, candidates must be registered in the federal Express Entry pool and must be eligible for at least one of 3 federal Economic programs:</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Federal Skilled Worker requires applicants to have, at least a high school diploma, as well as at least one year of continuous full-time, skilled work experience. Work experience is considered skilled if obtained in a position at National Occupational Classification (NOC) Skill Level 0, A, or B. Candidates must also demonstrate language proficiency in English or French consistent with Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 7.<br>2. Canadian Experience Class has no minimum education requirement. CEC candidates must have at least one year of full-time Canadian skilled work experience and the work experience does not have to be continuous, but it must have been gained within the 3 years before the application. Work experience is considered skilled if obtained in a position at NOC Skill Level 0, A, or B. Candidates must also show language proficiency in English or French consistent with CLB level 7.<br>3. Federal Skilled Trades has no minimum education requirement. FST candidates must have a minimum of 2 years of full-time work experience in a skilled trade occupation. Candidates must also have either an offer of employment to work in a skilled trade in Canada or a certificate of qualification in their skilled trade issued by a Canadian authority. Candidates must also demonstrate language proficiency in English or French at CLB Level 5 for speaking and listening and CLB 4 for reading and writing.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 2. PEI Labour Impact</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Foreign workers and recent graduates can apply for provincial nomination through one of Prince Edward Island’s Labour Impact streams.<br>1. Skilled Workers in PEI<br>2. Skilled Workers Outside Canada<br>3. Critical Worker<br>4. International Graduate</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> A. Skilled Workers in PEI</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The Skilled Worker in PEI stream of the Prince Edward Island Provincial Nomination Program (PEI PNP) welcomes foreign workers currently employed in PEI to apply for a provincial nomination for a fast-tracked path to permanent residence to fill the high demand for skilled positions that cannot currently be met through the local labour force.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. To be eligible for the Skilled Worker in PEI stream, candidates have to be living and working in PEI on a valid work permit.<br>2. Candidates must have a full-time, permanent job offer from an employer in PEI. The position must be classified as National Occupational Classification (NOC) Skill Level 0, A, or B.<br>\r\n3. Candidates need to demonstrate sufficient language proficiency in English or French to be able to perform their job duties. For this, you can take an official language test demonstrating proficiency consistent with Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 4.<br>4. Candidates must have at least completed a two-year post-secondary degree or diploma.<br>5. Candidates must have at least two years of full-time work experience in the past five years.<br>6. Candidates must be between 18 to 59 years old to be eligible to apply to this stream.<br>7. Candidates must meet the settlement funds requirement as determined by IRCC.<br>8. Candidates must demonstrate an intention to reside in PEI.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">B. Skilled Workers Outside Canada</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Foreign workers who are currently outside of Canada and have received a NOC Skill Level 0, A, or B position from an eligible employer is eligible to apply for the Skilled Worker Outside Canada stream of the Prince Edward Island Provincial Nomination Program (PEI PNP).</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. To be eligible, candidates must have a full-time, permanent job offer from an employer in PEI. The position must be classified as National Occupational Classification (NOC) Skill Level 0, A, or B. The employers making the job offer must contact the PEI immigration office and have the job offer approved.<br>2. Candidates need to demonstrate that they have sufficient language proficiency in English or French to be able to perform their job duties. This can be demonstrated through an official language test demonstrating proficiency consistent with Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 4.<br>3. Candidates must have at least completed a two-year post-secondary degree or diploma.<br>4. Candidates must have at least two years of full-time work experience in the past five years.<br>5. Candidates must be between 18 and 59 years old to be eligible to apply to this stream.<br>6. Candidates must meet the settlement funds requirement as determined by IRCC.\r\n7. Candidates must demonstrate an intention to reside in PEI.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> C. Critical Worker</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Requirements </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. To be eligible, candidates must have worked in PEI for at least six months for the PEI employer making the job offer. The candidate must have a valid work permit authorizing them to work for the PEI employer.<br>2. Candidates must have a permanent, full-time job offer from their current PEI employer. The job offer must be in a National Occupational Classification (NOC) Skill Level C or D occupation.<br>3. All candidates must have official language test results demonstrating proficiency in English or French consistent with Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 4.<br>4. Candidates must have at least completed secondary school.<br>5. Candidates must have at least two years of work experience or education relevant to their job offer in the past five years.<br>6. Candidates must be between 18 and 59 years old to be eligible to apply to this stream.<br>7. Candidates must meet the settlement funds requirement as determined by IRCC.<br>8. Candidates must demonstrate an intention to reside in PEI.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> D. International Graduate</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Recent graduates from an approved PEI post-secondary institution who are currently working in the province with a valid Post-Graduate Work Permit can get the advantage of the International Graduate program.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Requirement</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. Candidates must have graduated from a minimum two-year program at a publicly-funded post-secondary institution in PEI and have been working in PEI for at least 6 months in a position that is directly related to their PEI post-secondary education.<br>2. Candidates must have a full-time, permanent job offer from their current PEI employer. The job offer must be for a position classified as National Occupational Classification (NOC) Skill Level 0, A, or B.<br>3. Candidates must have sufficient ability to communicate in English or French.<br>4. Candidates must have completed a minimum two-year post-secondary program in PEI.<br>5. Candidates must have at least six months of experience working in PEI.<br>6. Candidates must be between 18 and 59 years old to be eligible to apply to this stream.<br>7. Candidates must meet the settlement funds requirement as determined by IRCC.\r\n8. Candidates must demonstrate an intention to reside in PEI.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 3. PEI Business Impact</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Whether establishing a business with 100% ownership or investing in a new or established PEI business, individuals wishing to immigrate to Canada on a business visa may take advantage of the Business Impact stream of the PEI PNP. They may also choose to obtain a work permit by investing in a PEI business, which will provide a faster transition to their new life in Canada and PEI.<br>1. Work Permit<br>2. 100% Ownership (closed)<br>3. Partial Ownership (closed)\r\n </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">A. Work Permit</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">Individuals wishing to live and operate a business in PEI may take advantage of the Prince Edward Island Provincial Nomination Program (PEI PNP) Work Permit Stream.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> Requirements</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">1. To be eligible for the PEI Work Permit stream, candidates must provide official language test results demonstrating language proficiency in English or French consistent with Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 4. <br>2. Candidates must have completed at least secondary school education. <br>\r\n3. Since the Work Permit stream is a Business Impact immigration program, candidates must have work experience that demonstrates management skills and business ownership experience. <br>4. Candidates for the Work Permit stream must have a personal net worth of at least $600,000 CAD. They must come to Canada on a work permit and operate a business for at least one year before they will receive a provincial nomination for permanent residence. Candidates must sign a performance agreement with the province.<br>[Performance Agreement: A performance agreement is an agreement signed with PEI that outlines the conditions under which the candidate will receive a nomination for permanent residence.\r\nPEI will issue a provincial nomination to the candidate if the following conditions are met:<br>1. Invest at least $150,000 CAD in the business;<br>2. Maintain a residence and actively manage the business from within PEI;<br>3. Operate the business for at least 12 consecutive months, and;<br>4. Provide financial statements that detail at least $75,000 CAD in eligible operating expenses.]<br>5. Candidates must be between 21 and 59 years old to be eligible to apply to this stream. <br>6. Candidates must demonstrate an intention to reside in PEI. </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\">Benefits </span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">There are plenty of reasons to invest in Prince Edward Island:\r\n</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 1. Low-Cost Location</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">According to the KPMG Study on business costs, Prince Edward Island is one of the lowest-cost locations for business. You will get a friendly environment, highly qualified personnel, communication, and business infrastructure.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 2. Peaceful Environment</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">In Prince Edward Island people live in an environment that offers big opportunities, affordable housing, less traffic, peaceful communities, amazing schools, great public healthcare, and a lot more. There you will find a proper work-life balance lifestyle that is very rare to find in this day and age. Prince Edward Island also has a very welcoming environment with fresh and clean sandy white beaches.\r\n </span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> 3. Strategic Location</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">The prime location of Prince Edward Island offers excellent access to North American and European markets with year-round ports, major air cargo routes, and high-bulk land transportation as it sits between Nova Scotia, New Brunswick, and Newfoundland.</span></span></p><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"background: white; margin: 15.0pt 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,style=\"font-size: 10px;serif; color: black;\"> How can Triple I business Help</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: ‘georgia’,serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 20px; font-family: ‘georgia’,serif; mso-bidi-font-family: \'georgia\'; color: black;\">At Triple I Business, we have the expertise to help you navigate the difficulties of these programs and help you choose correctly. We help you with:<br>1. Required documents for the immigration.<br>2. Complete processing of your application.<br>3.\r\nFilling out forms, submitting documentation, and filing applications.<br>4.Timely Updates & follow up on the process.\r\nAssistance in finding jobs in Canada.<br>With our years of experience in immigration, Triple I Business can help you file an application that has the highest chance of success. Contact one of our consultants today for guidance.\r\n</span></span></p><br>', 'Prince Edward Island(PEI) | Provincial Nominee Program | Requirements', 'Prince Edward Island(PEI) | PEI PNP | PEI Express Entry | PEI Labour Impact | PEI Business Impact | PEI Requirements | Benefits', 'Through Prince Edward Island PNP Program candidates can get a chance to live, study, & work. Check your requirements according to the streams.', 'Prince Edward island PNP', NULL, NULL, 'Prince Edward island PNP');
